      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">This document presents the NIST Federated Cloud Reference
                Architecture model. This actor/role- based model used the guiding principles of the
                NIST Cloud Computing Reference Architecture to develop an eleven component model.
                This document describes these components individually and how they function as an
                ensemble. There are many possible deployments and governance options which lend
                themselves to create a suite of federation options from simple to complex. The
                basics of cloud federation can be described through the interactions of the actors
                in a layered three planes representation of trust, security, and resource sharing
                and usage. A discussion on possible future standards and use cases are also
                described in great detail.</abstract>
